content_text:
Adobe has agreed to a $150M settlement over claims it made subscriptions like Photoshop too difficult for customers to cancel

• They must pay a $75M civil fine

• They also have to provide $75M in free services to customers

(via 
@Reuters
)

'Arc Raiders' has started replacing AI voices with human ones 

The CEO admits they are 'better' 

"There is a quality difference. A real professional actor is better than AI; that’s just how it is"

(via 
@GIBiz
)

A theater in Japan displayed real logs gnawed on by beavers to promote Pixar’s ‘Hoppers’ 

(via 
